<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="delighted-adj">delighted <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'laɪtɪd/    美 /dɪ'laɪtɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>高兴的；快乐的</strong></h4>
<p>very pleased and happy：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a delighted look 
高兴的神情</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) delighted at / by / with:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was delighted at the news of her wedding.
我很高兴听到她婚礼的消息。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) delighted to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The professor was delighted to find that the project had been finished by the students independently.
教授高兴地发现学生们已独立完成了该项目。</p><footer>2015 湖北</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) delighted + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’re delighted (that) you’re coming to work with us.
我们很高兴你要来和我们一起工作。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 4</footer></div>

<p>注: 不能用very修饰delighted。  </p></div>